{
  "stem": "3085.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And I think it was the afternoon when we were [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] de-trained and sort of lined up on a platform of some, some kind of a ramp at Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And again, we still didn't have any idea what kind of a place it was.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, we had-- we never heard-- I mean, I recall seeing, or my mother seeing actually a sign saying 'Auschwitz.' But, but, I mean, it didn't mean a thing.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And at that point, we were lining up.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were-- we saw, of course, those strange-looking people with, with prisoners' garb, you know, with the striped garb.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Again, we didn't know what to make of it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And, and there was quite a bit of commotion.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the SS, of course, were not very helpful.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And as we were lining up there, an SS officer came along, he sort of went along the line there, the column, and, and called out 'Zwillinge, Zwillinge.' And that means 'twins' in German.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I didn't know, either, [LAUGHS] at the time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My mother, of course, spoke German.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And she knew what it meant.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So she put up her hand or whatever and pointed to us, that we are twins.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And that-- so the German officer said for us to get out-- get out of the line.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And, of course, I didn't know at that time that, that that officer was Mengele.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And, and my mother was hesitant.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But I think she had the feeling that it's for the better.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Previous to actually arriving in Auschwitz, I recall vividly that she told us, both my brother and I, that if anything happens and we're separated, we should claim that we're not 11 years old, but only nine years old.",
      "word_count": 39
    }
  ],
